# certs/README.md — Certificate structure for raas-onboarding curriculum
#
# Generated by Topic 3 (PKI Fundamentals) openssl commands.
# These certs are reused in Topics 4 (RadSec) and 5 (EAP-TLS/TTLS).
#
# Directory layout (populated after running Topic 3 commands):
#
# certs/
#   ca/
#     ca.key       ← Root CA private key      (KEEP SECRET)
#     ca.crt       ← Root CA certificate      (distribute to all peers)
#     ca.srl       ← Serial counter           (auto-created by openssl)
#     dh           ← DH parameters            (used for PFS)
#   server/
#     server.key   ← Server private key       (KEEP SECRET)
#     server.csr   ← Server CSR               (intermediate, can delete)
#     server.crt   ← Server certificate       (presented to clients)
#   client/
#     client.key   ← Client private key       (KEEP SECRET)
#     client.csr   ← Client CSR               (intermediate, can delete)
#     client.crt   ← Client certificate       (presented by supplicant)
#
# Quick generation (run from repo root):
#   See topic-03-pki.md for the full step-by-step openssl commands.
